quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  44,1,"Hā Mīm<sup>1</sup>.","[1] See footnote 2:1."
  44,2,"By the clear Book.",""
  44,3,"Indeed, We sent it<sup>2</sup> down on a blessed night, We have been warning about.","[2] The revelation of the Qur’an started on the Night of Decree (al-Qadr) in the month of Ramadān, the 9th month of the lunar calendar. The Night of Decree is better than one thousand months. See (97:1 and 2:185)."
  44,4,"On that night, every matter of wisdom is determined<sup>3</sup>","[3] The angels record and descend with whatever Allah has decreed for the coming year, according to what is inscribed in the Preserved Tablet."
  44,5,"by Our command. We have always sent messengers.",""
  44,6,"as a mercy from your Lord. He is indeed the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing,",""
  44,7,"Lord of the heavens and earth and all that is between them, if only you had sure faith.",""
  44,8,"None has the right to be worshiped except Him, Who gives life and causes death – your Lord, and the Lord of your forefathers.",""
  44,9,"But they are in doubt, amusing themselves.",""
  44,10,"So wait for a day when the sky will bring forth a visible smoke<sup>4</sup>,","[4] Referring to the drought that affected the pagans of Makkah severely, so they came to the Prophet (ﷺ), begging him to supplicate Allah to remove the affliction from them."
  44,11,"that will overwhelm the people. This is a painful punishment!",""
  44,12,"[They will cry,] “Our Lord, remove the punishment from us; we will surely believe!”",""
  44,13,"How will they take heed, when a messenger who explained things clearly has already come to them?",""
  44,14,"Then they turned away from him and said, “[He is] a madman, taught by others.”",""
  44,15,"We shall hold the punishment back for a while, but you will surely return [to disbelief].",""
  44,16,"On the Day when We seize [them] with the greatest assault, We will surely exact retribution.",""
  44,17,"Indeed, We tested the people of Pharaoh before them, when a noble messenger came to them,",""
  44,18,"[saying], “Hand over to me the slaves of Allah<sup>5</sup>. I am indeed a trustworthy messenger to you,","[5] i.e., the Children of Israel."
